title: The Inside Bar Trading Strategy | Fast Tutorial in Profectus AI
text: let's create a profitable strategy together log in to Profectus AI and get started let's go to template's where strategies are pre built for us here you can see five trading strategies and five management styles as a begin ner let's focus on the strategies first select the inside bar breakout strategy this is a trading strategy for gold on the daily time frame click apply template great and then click on ex 5 export i have uploaded the exported file into MetaTrader 5 if you don't have MetaTrader 5 please watch that tutor ial first let's run a back test for this strategy i drag and drop the algorithm i select the gold symbol and daily time frame i select visual mode to see the charts this is the strategy in action let's build it in Profectus AI from scratch so we can learn to create a trading strategy first we need to understand the logic this strategy uses the inside bar pattern this is how that pattern works you have two candles tick's candle one which is the most recently closed candle and candle two which is the candle before candle one we call this candle id one and candle id two the inside bar pattern happens when candle one high is lower than candle two high and at the same time the candle one low is higher than the candle two low here you clearly see that candle id 2 is higher and lower than candle id 1 confirming the inside bar pattern in Profectus AI ai we create this with two trade rule blocks in block one we confirm that candle high two is higher than candle high one in block two we confirm that candle low 2 is lower than candle low one all right now we know the trading rules let's walk through the whole strategy together we want this algorithm to run at 2 at night we want to check if it is tuesday wednesday thursday or friday then the inside bar logic is checked then we check if we don't have more than five trades open at this time then we place a buy pending order the order is placed at the candle high of candle 1 this is the inside bar remember we use a stop loss of half a of the current price we use a target of five times the stop loss size this is called a risk to reward of 1 to 5 at the same time we also place a sell pending order but then at the low of the inside bar the stop loss and target placement is similar to the buy pending order we also have the same tree for monday we had to split this and change the candle id logic because we have the weekend in between friday and monday sometimes a broker has sunday candles tick's so this was the right way to solve that problem then we want to add trade management we use four blocks for this select trades check profit once per trade modify the stop loss or target go ahead and study how this works by opening the blocks thank you for watching make sure to like sub scribe and comment your questions

title: General Price Action Explainer
text: why care for price action price action trading cuts through the noise by concentrating on the market's most fundamental element price price action is the most powerful tool in trading but most traders still traded manually he sit ating doubt ing them sel and missing move therefore let me give you a very quick crash course about candles tick's and price action patterns before we dive into the nitty-gritties of each price action let's take a look here at this chart we're looking on the daily time frame of gold traded against the us dollar if you're not familiar with candles tick's you're probably familiar with the line chart you see on the news they are telling you one single information which is usually the closing price of that day so this is just one point of information for
